    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The test currently only asserts that an error occurred and that it\u2019s not a *codersdk.Error. To make the transport-error case deterministic and ensure the injected RoundTripper is actually the source of the failure, keep a sentinel error and assert ErrorIs on it.",
    "commit_id": "91e1c7944084e666f3cf343b498bd268738b37fb",
    "created_at": "2026-06-08T14:07:53Z",
    "diff_hunk": "@@ -271,13 +273,13 @@ func TestResolveWorkspace(t *testing.T) {\n \tt.Run(\"TransportError\", func(t *testing.T) {\n \t\tt.Parallel()\n \n-\t\t// Close the server immediately so the transport layer fails.\n-\t\tsrv := httptest.NewServer(http.NotFoundHandler())\n-\t\tsrvURL, err := url.Parse(srv.URL)\n+\t\tbaseURL, err := url.Parse(\"http://example.com\")\n \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n-\t\tsrv.Close()\n-\n-\t\tclient := codersdk.New(srvURL)\n+\t\tclient := codersdk.New(baseURL, codersdk.WithHTTPClient(&http.Client{\n+\t\t\tTransport: testutil.RoundTripperFunc(func(*http.Request) (*http.Response, error) {\n+\t\t\t\treturn nil, xerrors.New(\"transport error\")\n+\t\t\t}),\n+\t\t}))\n \n \t\t_, err = client.ResolveWorkspace(t.Context(), uuid.NewString())\n \t\trequire.Error(t, err)",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/coder/coder/pull/26132#discussion_r3373832679",
